Name: The name of the language.
MustCombine: Tells the user the number of elements they must combine.
MaxCombine: Tells the user the most elements they can combine.
DoesntExist: Tells the user that a single element doesn't exist.
DoesntExistMultiple: Tells the user that multiple elements don't exist.
DoesntExistJoiner: The word that joins the don't have message, like in "a, b, and c" this would be "and".
DontHave: Tells the user they don't have a single element.
DontHaveMultiple: Tells the user they don't have a set of elements.
DontHaveJoiner: The word that joins the don't have message, like in "a, b, or c" this would be "or".
YouMade: Tells the user they made an element.
YouHave: The the user they made an element, but they already have it.
ComboNoExist: Tells the user the combo doesn't exist and they can suggest a result.
NewsChannel: Tell the user the news channel was updated.
VotingChannel: Tell the user the voting channel was updated.
VoteCount: Tell the user the vote count was updated.
PollCount: Tell the user the poll count was updated.
ModRole: Tell the user the moderator role was updated.
UserColorReset: Tell the user their color was reset.
HexMustBe6: Tell the user that a hex color must be 6 characters.
UserColor: Tell the user their color was updated.
Language: Tell the user the server language was set.
PlayChannelNew: Tell the user a channel was marked as a play channel
PlayChannelRemove: Tell the user a channel was marked as not being a play channel
CatNameBlank: Tell the user the category name can't be blank.
CatNameTooLong: Tell the user the category name is too long.
CatNoExist: Tell the user the category doesn't exist.
CatAlreadyExist: Tells the user the category already exists.
NotInCat: Tell the user the element isn't in the category.
Categorized: Tell the user the elements were categorized.
SuggestCategorized: Tell the user the element was suggested to be categorized.
SuggestCategorizedMult: Tell the user the elements were suggested to be categorized.
CategorizeMultSuggestCategorized: Tell the user the elements were categorized and one was suggested to be categorized.
CategorizeMultSuggestCategorizedMult: Tell the user the elements were categorized and were suggested to be categorized.
UnCategorized: Tell the user the elements were un-categorized.
SuggestUnCategorized: Tell the user the element was suggested to be un-categorized.
SuggestUnCategorizedMult: Tell the user the elements were suggested to be un-categorized.
UnCategorizeMultSuggestUnCategorized: Tell the user the elements were un-categorized and one was suggested to be un-categorized.
UnCategorizeMultSuggestUnCategorizedMult: Tell the user the elements were un-categorized and were suggested to be un-categorized.
ViewMoreStats: The message in the View More Stats button.
ElemCategories: The title of the /get categories embed.
NameDownloadedCat: Tell the user which category they downloaded.
CatSentToDMs: Tell the user that the category was sent to their DMs.
InvalidSort: Tell the user the chosen sort is not valid in the current context.
AllCategories: The title of the embed shown when listing all categories using /cat without a specified category.
NewAIIdea: The message in the New AI Generated Idea button.
FailedAIGenerate: Tell the user the AI could not generate a combo.
SuggestIdea: Tells the user they can suggest a result for the generated combo.
YourAIIdea: Tells the user what their AI generated combo is.
ElemFound: The title of the /get found embed.
NewHint: The message in the New Hint button.
InvHintNoElem: Tells the user they must input an element to get an inverse hint.
HintElem: The title of the hint embed.
InvHintElem: The title of the inverse hint embed.
HintCountHasElem: The footer of the hint embed saying how many combos are in the hint and that the user has the element.
HintCountNoHasElem: The footer of the hint embed saying how many combos are in the hint and that the user does not have the element
ElemSort: The title of the element sort embed.
InfoExpand: The message in the Expand button.
InfoCollapse: The message in the Collapse buton.
InfoAdditionalElemCats: The message that replaces any categories past the third in the info page, telling the user how many more categories the element is in besides those three.
StarterElemCreateTime: The message that should be displayed as the creation time of the starter elements.
InfoCommenter: The label for the Commenter on the info page.
InfoImager: The label for the Imager on the info page.
InfoColorer: The label for the Colorer on the info page.
InfoComment: The label for the Comment on the info page.
InfoCombosUsedIn: The label for the number of combos an element is used in on the info page.
InfoCombosMadeWith: The label for the number of combos an element can be created with on the info page.
InfoUsersFoundBy: The label for the number of users who have found an element on the info page.
InfoCreator: The label for the Creator on the info page.
InfoCreateTime: The label for the Creation Time on the info page.
InfoColor: The label for the Color on the info page.
InfoTreeSize: The label for the Tree Size on the info page.
InfoComplexity: The label for the Complexity on the info page.
InfoDifficulty: The label for the Difficulty on the info page.
InfoTitle: The title of the info page, also displaying the element.
InfoElemIDUserHasElem: The element ID, and the message saying that the user has the element.
InfoElemIDUserNoHasElem: The element ID, and the message saying that the user does not have the element.
InfoElemProgress: The label for the user's progress to the element on the info page.
InfoElemCats: The label for the Categories on the info page.
InvalidElemID: Tells the user that the element ID they inputted is invalid.
ResetUserInv: Tells the user that the inventory of the specified user was sucessfully reset.
DownloadedInvUserServer: Tells the user whose inventory was downloaded, and what server it was downloaded from.
SentInvToDMs: Tells the user that their downloaded inventory was sent to their DMs.
LbImage: The name given to the Leaderboard Image.
UserInventory: The title of the inventory embed, displaying whose inventory it is, the number of elements they have, and the percentage of all elements that they have.
LbTitleElem: The title given to element leaderboards.
NewIdea: The message in the New Idea button.
HaveNoElemsInCat: Tells the user that they have no elements in the specified category.
FailedIdea: Tells the user that no idea could be generated with the given parameters.
YourIdea: Tells the user what their random combo is.
NoResults: Tells the user that no results were found for the given search parameters.
ElemSearch: The title of the Element Search embed, also displaying the number of elements found with the search.
ElemNameCannotStartWithQuestionMark: Tells the user that the suggestion cannot start with a question mark.
ElemNameMaxLength: Tells the user the maximum number of characters they can have in an element name.
ElemNameForbiddenChar: Tells the user the characters in their suggested element name that cannot be in element names.
NoSuggestElemName: Tells the user that their suggestion cannot be empty.
MustSuggestInPlayChannel: Tells the user that they can only suggest in play channels.
ComboHasResult: Tells the user that the combo they are trying to suggest a result for already has a result.
SuggestedElem: Tells the user what combo they just suggested.
BreakdownTitle: The title of the breakdown embed.
InvBreakdownTitle: The title of the inventory breakdown embed.
GiveElem: Tells the user they successfully gave the specified element.
GiveCat: Tells the user they successfully gave every element in the specified category.
GiveAll: Tells the user they successfully gave every element to the specified user.
GraphLayoutInvalid: Tells the user the specified graph layout is invalid.
GraphTooBigForLayout: Tells the user the graph is too big for the specified layout.
GraphOutputInvalid: Tells the user the specified output type is invalid.
SentGraphToDMs: Tells the user the graph was sent to their DMs.
GraphNotRendered: Tells the user the graph was not rendered by the bot.
NameGraphElem: Tells the user which element/category was graphed.
SentNotationToDMs: Tells the user the notation was sent to their DMs.
NotationTooLong: Tells the user the notation was sent as a file to their DMs due to being too long for a normal message.
NameNotationElem: Tells the user which element the notation is for.
NameNotationCat: Tells the user which category the notation is for.
SentPathToDMs: Tells the user the path as sent to their DMs.
PathTooLong: Tells the user the path was sent as a file to their DMs due to being too long for a normal message.
NamePathElem: Tells the user which element the path is for.
NamePathCat: Tells the user which category the path is for.
NewElemPoll: The title of polls for new elements.
NewComboPoll: The title of polls for new element combinations.
NewMarkPoll: The title of polls for element marks.
ElemImagePoll: The title of polls for element images.
AddCatPoll: The title of polls for element categorizations.
RmCatPoll: The title of polls for element un-categorizations.
DelCatPoll: The title of polls for category deletions.
CatImagePoll: The title of polls for category images.
ElemColorPoll: The title of polls for element colors.
ResetCatColorPoll: The title of polls for category color resets.
SetCatColorPoll: The title of polls for category color changes.
MoreElemsPoll: The description to put when the number of elements displayed in the poll is shortened.
IntersectPoll: The title of polls for category intersections.
UnionPoll: The title of polls for category unions.
DiffPoll: The title of polls for category differences.
NewNote: The line displaying the new element mark in polls.
OldNote: The line displaying the old element mark in polls.
NewImage: The text on the link to the new image in polls.
OldImage: The text on the link to the old image in polls.
CatPollElems: The line with the title of the list of elements in categorization/decategorization polls.
CatPollCat: The line with the category in categorization/decategorization polls.
ShownOnLeft: The text denoting that the color of elements/categories is shown on the left color bar of the embed.
OldColor: The line with the old color in polls.
PollCreatorText: The line denoting the suggester of polls.
NewElemNews: The news message for when a new element is created.
NewComboNews: The news message for when a new combination for an element is created.
SignedElemNews: The news message for successful element mark polls.
AddedImageNews: The news message when an element is first given an image.
ChangedImageNews: The news message when an element's image is changed.
ColoredElemNews: The news message when an element's color is changed.
RejectedPollNews: The news message when a poll is rejected.
RejectedPollDM: The DM to the user whose poll was rejected saying which server the poll was in, how many upvotes/downvotes it had, and the poll itself.
AddCatNews: The news message when a single element is added to a category.
AddCatMultNews: The news message when multiple elements are added to a category.
RmCatNews: The news message when a single element is removed from a category.
RmCatMultNews: The news message when multiple elements are removed from a category.
ResetCatColorNews: The news message when a category's color is reset.
SetCatColorNews: The news message when a category's color is changed.
MaxMarkLength: Tells the user that a creator mark must be below 2400 characters.
MarkChanged: Tells the user that they changed the mark of their element.
MarkSuggested: Tells the user that a poll was created to change the mark of the element.
ImageAdded: Tells the user that they added an image of their element.
ImageChanged: Tells the user that they changed the image of their element.
ImageSuggested: Tells the user that a poll was created to change the image of the element.
ElemColorChanged: Tells the user that they changed the color of their element.
ElemColorSuggested: Tells the user that a poll was created to change the color of the element.
CatImageSuggested: Tells the user that a poll was created to change the image of the category.
CatColorSuggested: Tells the user that a poll was created to change the color of the category.
MustAttachImage: Tell the user they must attach an image.
AddCatMustHaveSeparator: Tell the user they must separate the category name and the elements to add to the category with a vertical bar.
RmCatMustHaveSeparator: Tell the user they must separate the category name and the elements to remove from the category with a vertical bar.
MarkMustHaveSeparator: Tell the user they must separate the element name and the element mark with a vertical bar.
PingMessage: The message given by the !ping command, also displaying the latency of the bot's response.
MustHaveAdmin: Tell the user they must have the Administrator permission.
MustHaveAdminOrModRole: Tell the user they must have the Administrator permission or the server moderator role.
MustHaveElemForPath: Tell the user they must have the element to get its path.
MustHaveCatForPath: Tell the user they must have every element in the category to get its path.
MustHaveElemOrID: Tell the user that they must input either an element or an element ID.
CannotHaveBothElemAndID: Tell the user that they cannot input both an element and an element ID.
IDCannotBeNegative: Tell the user their element ID cannot be negative.
DBNoCombo: Tell the user the combo doesn't exist.
PollNoExist: Tell the user the poll doesn't exist.
CalculatingPing: Tell the user that the bot is calculating the ping.
SentWordCloud: Tell the user the word cloud was sent in their DMs.
WordCloudElem: Tell the user which element the word cloud is for.
WordCloudDimensionsTooLow: Tell the user the dimensions of the word cloud are too low.
WordCloudDimensionsTooHigh: Tell the user the dimensions of the word cloud are too high.
